main event: Two witnesses observed a clear orange colored object in the WNW sky for 1 hour and 3 minutes on June 20, 1966, in Centerville, Ohio.
interesting points: The orange object moved downward approximately 6 degrees before disappearing,The sighting lasted for over an hour,The object was described as clearly visible during the observation,No photographs were taken during the sighting,The report indicates that the object appeared solid.
sighted object: orange colored object in the sky
